                    "day": null,
                    "year": 2016
                }
            },
            "description": "Photocatalytic water splitting represents a promising strategy for clean, low-cost, and environmental friendly production of H2 by utilizing solar energy. \nIn this project, novel strategies to design photocatalysts and novel nanomaterials for efficient production of hydrogen are comprehensively reviewed based on fundamental principles. \nFurthermore, seeking cheap and earth-abundant performant materials is indispensable to achieve cost-effective photocatalytic water splitting. \nFinally, this review is concluded with the proposal of a theoretically efficient photocatalytic system considering the presented design guidelines. ",
